      <h3 class="tier-heading">Bug Fixes</h3>
      <ul class="docs-list">
        <li><strong>Top bar content alignment</strong> — <code>arc-top-bar</code> now uses the same centering strategy as <code>arc-container</code> (<code>max-width</code> + <code>margin-inline: auto</code> + <code>padding-inline</code>) so nav content aligns pixel-perfect with page content at every viewport width. Consumers no longer need <code>::part(topbar)</code> padding overrides.</li>
      </ul>
